# Error Handling

## Backend — NestJS exceptions

Always throw typed NestJS exceptions. Never throw raw `Error` or return error objects.

```ts
// ✅ correct
import { NotFoundException, BadRequestException, InternalServerErrorException } from '@nestjs/common';

async findOne(id: string) {
  const run = await this.prisma.scenarioRun.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  if (!run) throw new NotFoundException(`ScenarioRun ${id} not found`);
  return run;
}

// ❌ wrong — raw Error leaks stack trace to client
throw new Error('not found');

// ❌ wrong — returning error objects bypasses global filter
return { error: 'not found', code: 404 };
```

### Exception map
| Situation | Exception |
|-----------|-----------|
| Resource not found | `NotFoundException` (404) |
| Invalid input | `BadRequestException` (400) |
| Unauthorized | `UnauthorizedException` (401) |
| Forbidden | `ForbiddenException` (403) |
| Conflict (duplicate) | `ConflictException` (409) |
| Unexpected error | `InternalServerErrorException` (500) |

## Backend — service catch blocks

```ts
// ✅ correct pattern — log + Sentry + rethrow
async create(dto: RunScenarioDto) {
  try {
    return await this.prisma.scenarioRun.create({ data: dto });
  } catch (err) {
    const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
    this.logger.error({ event: 'scenario_create_failed', error: message });
    Sentry.captureException(err, { tags: { domain: 'scenarios' } });
    throw new InternalServerErrorException('Failed to create scenario run');
  }
}

// ❌ wrong — swallowed error
} catch (err) {
  console.log(err);
  return null;
}

// ❌ wrong — leaking internal error message to client
throw new InternalServerErrorException(err.message);
```

## Backend — global exception filter

The `AllExceptionsFilter` in `src/common/filters/` is registered globally in `main.ts`.
Do NOT register additional filters per-controller — use the global one.

Response shape (enforced by filter):
```json
{
  "statusCode": 404,
  "message": "ScenarioRun abc not found",
  "path": "/api/scenarios/abc",
  "timestamp": "2026-04-22T..."
}
```

## Frontend — query error handling

```tsx
// ✅ correct — always handle isError
const { data, isLoading, isError, error } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['scenarios'],
  queryFn: fetchScenarios,
});

if (isError) {
  return (
    <p className="text-sm text-destructive">
      {(error as Error).message}
    </p>
  );
}
```

## Frontend — mutation error handling

```tsx
// ✅ correct
const mutation = useMutation({ mutationFn: runScenario });

{mutation.isError && (
  <p className="text-sm text-destructive">
    {(mutation.error as Error).message}
  </p>
)}

// ❌ wrong — silent failure
const mutation = useMutation({ mutationFn: runScenario });
// no error display
```

## Frontend — form validation errors

```tsx
// ✅ correct — show field-level errors from RHF
{errors.type && (
  <p className="text-sm text-destructive">{errors.type.message}</p>
)}

// ❌ wrong — alert() or console.error()
if (!isValid) alert('Please fix errors');
```

## Never log or expose
- Stack traces to API clients
- Database error messages (contain schema info)
- Internal service URLs or credentials
- User passwords or tokens in any log level
